{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#4689: type Inference incorrect of `DefineComponent` with `HTMLAttributes`",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:27:10.823256+00:00",
  "text": "type Inference incorrect of `DefineComponent` with `HTMLAttributes`\n\n### Version\r\n3.2.19\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n```ts\r\nconst props = {\r\n  propA: Number,\r\n  propB: [String, Number],\r\n  propC: {\r\n    type: String,\r\n    required: true,\r\n  },\r\n}\r\n\r\nconst Comp = defineComponent({\r\n  props,\r\n  setup() {\r\n    return <div></div>\r\n  },\r\n}) as unknown as DefineComponent<HTMLAttributes & typeof props>\r\n\r\nconst render = () => {\r\n  const onClick = () => {}\r\n  return <Comp propA={1} onClick={onClick}></Comp>\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n \r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25052421/134903842-99df30fb-a48d-4d7e-b2c0-6b00a4baa421.png)\r\n\r\nType 'number' is not assignable to type 'NumberConstructor'.\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
